"Satoshi owning a million bitcoin is just a widely spread myth. Someone named Sergio started that myth years ago and people just keep ignorantly repeating it as a fact. Nobody really knows how much bitcoin Satoshi actually owns. All we know for a fact is that Satoshi mined the genesis block (which can't be spent) and block 9. Other than that, all we can do is speculate.

There were 6 days between the genesis block being mined on January 3 and block 1 being mined on January 9 (while the difficulty was 1), so we know that Satoshi waited for other people to start mining before joining in himself.

Below are two examples of early bitcoin miners that were mining alongside Satoshi from the very beginning.
https://twitter.com/halfin/status/1110302988
https://twitter.com/druidian/status/1447833108355731462
https://stephanlivera.com/episode/314/

There is also a user on the bitcointalk forum that signed a message using the private key from a bitcoin address that was used to receive a 50 BTC coinbase transaction block reward in 2009."
